The paper presents a deep learning model for entity summarization over knowledge graphs, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper deals with knowledge representation and storage, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) as another possible sub-category. The model also uses scoring mechanisms to evaluate the relevance of triples, which relates to information retrieval and ranking, indicating cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a potential sub-category. Finally, the paper employs deep learning techniques, which aligns with cs.LG (Machine Learning).
